Commands:\n
continue Continue to the next break point.\n
disp [sysIdx:blkIdx | gcb] \n Display data of block at every stopping point.\n
ebreak Toggle break on solver errors.\n

elist m:mid [tid:TID] Display the system execution list(s) identified by the system method (mid) and tid (TID).
 elist <gcs | s:sysIdx> [mth] [tid:TID]

 elist <gcb | sysIdx:blkIdx> [mth] [tid:TID] 
 Display the system execution list(s) identified by the subsystem block (sysIdx:blkIdx), method (mth) and tid (TID).
emode Toggle execution between Normal and Accelerator modes.\n
etrace level Set the execution trace level (0=none, 3=everything).\n

help Display help on all sldebug commands.
 help cmd Display help for cmd.
 help time Display info on simulation time format.
ishow Set strace level to 4 (deprecated, use strace).\n
nanbreak Toggle break on non-finite (NaN,Inf) values.\n
next Step over the current simulation point.\n

probe Enters probe mode to display data for the current block.
 probe [gcb | sysIdx:blkIdx] 
 Probe data of block (sysIdx:blkIdx).

? Display help on all sldebug commands.\n
quit Abort the simulation.\n
rbreak Toggle break on solver reset requests.\n
run Stop debugging and finish the simulation.\n
strace level Set solver trace level (0=none, 4=everything).\n
slist Display the sorted list(s).\n
states Display current state values.\n
status [all] Display debugging actions in effect.\n

step [in | into] Go to the next simulation point.
 step over Step over the current simulation point.

 step top Go to the top of the next time step.
 step blockmth Go to the next block method.
stimes Display the sample time table of the model.\n
stop Stop execution.\n
systems Display a list of the model systems.\n
tbreak Clear time break point.\n tbreak t Break when the simulation time exceeds t.\n

Time is displayed as: 
 TM = <time while in Major step> 
 Tm = <time while in minor step> 
 Tr = <time while in solver reset> 
 Tz = <time at or just after zero crossing> 
 TzL= <time while in major step just before (at left post of) zero crossing> 
 TzR= <time while in major step at or just after (at right post of) zero crossing> 
 Ts = <time of successful integration step> 
 Tf = <time of failed integration step> 
 Tn = <time while in Newton iteration> (when using implicit solvers) 
 Tj = <time during Jacobian evaluation> (when using implicit solvers) 
Step size is displayed as: 
 Hm = <step size at the start of solver phase> 
 Hs = <successful integration step size> 
 Hf = <failed integration step size> 
 Hn = <step size during Newton iteration> (when using implicit solvers) 
 Hz = <value of 'TM - TzL' during zero crossing search> 
 Iz = <value of 'Tz - TzL' during zero crossing search>
trace <gcb | sysIdx:blkIdx> \n Add a trace point to display data of block as it is executed.\n
undisp <gcb | sysIdx:blkIdx> \n Remove a display point.\n
untrace <gcb | sysIdx:blkIdx> \n Remove a trace point.\n
where [detail] Display the current location in the simulation loop (detail=0 => minimum details).\n
xbreak Toggle break on failed integration step.\n
zcbreak Toggle break when zero crossing events are detected.\n
zclist Display the list of zero crossings signals.\n
